1
00:00:10,870 --> 00:00:17,280
<i>But if we reunite,
and I act like a stranger, that's your cue.</i>

2
00:00:21,550 --> 00:00:25,680
May I leave your order here,

3
00:00:26,520 --> 00:00:28,320
ma'am?

4
00:01:22,430 --> 00:01:25,000
- You sure?
- Huh?

5
00:01:25,000 --> 00:01:28,760
Don't you share this space with your husband?

6
00:01:36,930 --> 00:01:38,610
No.

7
00:01:40,370 --> 00:01:43,190
This is my bedroom, where I sleep alone.

8
00:01:46,760 --> 00:01:50,240
Things have gone unbelievably well
since we last spoke.

9
00:01:50,240 --> 00:01:51,830
Ouji...

10
00:01:54,060 --> 00:01:57,180
My husband has become kind,

11
00:01:57,180 --> 00:01:59,730
and work has come pouring in.

12
00:02:06,510 --> 00:02:08,640
But, I...

13
00:02:21,240 --> 00:02:25,730
[For once you've opened a door...]

14
00:02:30,300 --> 00:02:32,580
I want to see what lies beyond this.

15
00:02:57,650 --> 00:02:59,300
The time...

16
00:02:59,300 --> 00:03:01,240
We're still good.

17
00:03:01,240 --> 00:03:03,810
My next delivery
isn't for another 25 minutes.

18
00:03:26,450 --> 00:03:28,610
That feels amazing...

19
00:03:39,220 --> 00:03:43,680
<i>It was a mere 25 minutes of my life.</i>

20
00:04:39,900 --> 00:04:43,960
[Episode 10]

21
00:04:50,440 --> 00:04:52,820
I feel so relieved.

22
00:04:54,780 --> 00:04:56,860
That's a bit crude.

23
00:05:01,300 --> 00:05:03,020
I can write.

24
00:05:14,830 --> 00:05:17,600
<i>I reckon I won't see that man again.</i>

25
00:05:17,600 --> 00:05:21,320
<i>Nor will I ever tell my husband about this.</i>

26
00:05:21,320 --> 00:05:25,880
<i>But I don't regret what I've done.</i>

27
00:05:28,590 --> 00:05:30,860
If I had to make a comparison...

28
00:05:30,860 --> 00:05:33,530
[Ram3]

29
00:05:33,530 --> 00:05:39,690
"It felt like you were finally relieved
of being constipated"?

30
00:05:39,690 --> 00:05:40,870
Great comparison.

31
00:05:40,870 --> 00:05:43,130
But that's really what it felt like!

32
00:05:43,130 --> 00:05:48,010
Like, relieving yourself
after a long day of work.

33
00:05:48,010 --> 00:05:49,200
Oh gosh...

34
00:05:49,200 --> 00:05:51,240
Our resident author has a way with words.

35
00:05:53,400 --> 00:05:55,630
- In any case, I'm happy for you.
- Huh?

36
00:05:56,510 --> 00:06:01,310
I can tell the experience really helped you.

37
00:06:03,370 --> 00:06:06,680
Yeah, it probably did.

38
00:06:07,670 --> 00:06:12,400
Things were going well with Ouji,
and I was satisfied enough.

39
00:06:12,400 --> 00:06:17,740
I assumed I didn't need sex in my life.

40
00:06:17,740 --> 00:06:22,930
But I was only trying to delude myself.

41
00:06:22,930 --> 00:06:25,050
And the relief I felt after sex

42
00:06:25,050 --> 00:06:28,270
made that fact all the more obvious.

43
00:06:30,000 --> 00:06:37,050
All this time, I've wondered why
I couldn't have these experiences.

44
00:06:37,750 --> 00:06:41,970
It made me feel inferior to others.

45
00:06:43,260 --> 00:06:46,760
But now I see it was no big deal after all.

46
00:06:46,760 --> 00:06:50,430
I'm like, "that wasn't so hard", you know?

47
00:06:50,430 --> 00:06:56,960
Haru, that means it was a big deal to you.

48
00:06:58,640 --> 00:07:02,140
You think so?

49
00:07:04,800 --> 00:07:09,650
I've actually come to a similar revelation.

50
00:07:10,370 --> 00:07:13,210
About why I'm so attached to him.

51
00:07:13,210 --> 00:07:15,710
What, is your fling good in bed?

52
00:07:15,710 --> 00:07:17,360
Language, Akina.

53
00:07:17,360 --> 00:07:19,100
That's not entirely it.

54
00:07:19,100 --> 00:07:26,090
My husband is self-centered, even in bed.

55
00:07:26,090 --> 00:07:29,540
Doing it with him was never enjoyable.

56
00:07:29,540 --> 00:07:32,530
It always felt like an obligation of sorts.

57
00:07:32,530 --> 00:07:35,430
That sounds difficult.

58
00:07:35,430 --> 00:07:38,060
Which is why when I met my partner now,

59
00:07:39,470 --> 00:07:41,850
I felt fulfilled.

60
00:07:41,850 --> 00:07:43,440
Sexually?

61
00:07:43,440 --> 00:07:47,630
I mean, yes, that too.

62
00:07:48,380 --> 00:07:52,330
But I felt as though he saw me as a woman.

63
00:07:53,060 --> 00:07:56,600
As a human being, even.

64
00:07:56,600 --> 00:08:00,160
It was honestly comforting, in a way.

65
00:08:02,620 --> 00:08:04,310
I get it.

66
00:08:06,390 --> 00:08:11,080
I grew up with a low self-esteem,

67
00:08:11,080 --> 00:08:14,020
but I finally feel like that's changing.

68
00:08:14,850 --> 00:08:18,830
It's like I'm more confident now,
for some reason.

69
00:08:18,830 --> 00:08:24,300
See? It was a big deal for you.

70
00:08:27,470 --> 00:08:30,350
Meanwhile, mine's only tanking.

71
00:08:30,350 --> 00:08:31,410
Huh?

72
00:08:31,410 --> 00:08:35,820
My self-esteem.
It's about to hit rock bottom.

73
00:08:36,780 --> 00:08:43,280
Even though I feel
plenty comforted and fulfilled.

74
00:08:43,280 --> 00:08:46,370
Is this about the male "therapist"?

75
00:08:46,370 --> 00:08:49,350
Yeah. The "therapist".

76
00:08:49,350 --> 00:08:52,520
And I'm just a customer.

77
00:08:52,520 --> 00:08:56,350
I can't deny that.

78
00:08:56,350 --> 00:09:01,040
But you can't ask to meet in private, right?

79
00:09:01,040 --> 00:09:03,580
Because you wouldn't want to be rude.

80
00:09:03,580 --> 00:09:06,270
Nothing will happen
if you don't at least try.

81
00:09:06,270 --> 00:09:08,870
I see a one-night stand
has made you confident.

82
00:09:08,870 --> 00:09:11,070
It was a one-afternoon stand, mind you.

83
00:09:11,070 --> 00:09:13,880
What's the difference?

84
00:09:15,720 --> 00:09:18,010
I wonder if I'll be a customer forever.

85
00:09:23,300 --> 00:09:24,740
I gotta go.

86
00:09:24,740 --> 00:09:27,270
- Huh?
- I'm meeting him tonight.

87
00:09:28,050 --> 00:09:30,830
I think I'm getting used to this loop.

88
00:09:30,830 --> 00:09:33,760
I can't stop myself from wanting to see him.

89
00:09:46,300 --> 00:09:48,430
<i>How are you feeling?</i>

90
00:09:51,500 --> 00:09:54,440
<i>I'm fine. It's been three weeks
since the operation.</i>

91
00:09:54,440 --> 00:09:56,730
<i>You worrywart.</i>

92
00:10:02,110 --> 00:10:04,720
<i>Can I call you?</i>

93
00:10:04,720 --> 00:10:06,080
<i>Sure.</i>

94
00:10:11,800 --> 00:10:13,190
Hello?

95
00:10:13,190 --> 00:10:15,310
Hey there.

96
00:10:15,310 --> 00:10:18,180
You're outside? Is everything okay?

97
00:10:18,700 --> 00:10:21,680
I need to be outside to go out the house.

98
00:10:21,680 --> 00:10:23,420
I guess...

99
00:10:23,420 --> 00:10:25,440
I promise I'm fine, okay?

100
00:10:25,440 --> 00:10:28,600
I can't help it, I worry about you.

101
00:10:29,410 --> 00:10:31,080
Thanks.

102
00:10:32,070 --> 00:10:36,180
Why did you want to call?

103
00:10:36,180 --> 00:10:40,190
Big news.
I'm going to be on the cover of a magazine!

104
00:10:43,020 --> 00:10:46,230
<i>I'm counting on you to style me, Fuyumi.</i>

105
00:10:47,870 --> 00:10:49,590
<i>Fuyumi?</i>

106
00:10:52,200 --> 00:10:54,000
Sorry, I was just so shocked.

107
00:10:55,020 --> 00:10:56,920
Congratulations.

108
00:10:56,920 --> 00:10:59,860
Will you come celebrate with me sometime?

109
00:11:00,600 --> 00:11:01,760
Sure.

110
00:11:01,760 --> 00:11:03,350
<i>Thanks.</i>

111
00:11:03,350 --> 00:11:07,690
I'll reach out again once I'm home, okay?

112
00:11:07,690 --> 00:11:09,200
Talk to you soon.

113
00:11:31,920 --> 00:11:33,580
Good evening.

114
00:11:33,580 --> 00:11:34,850
You ran here?

115
00:11:34,850 --> 00:11:36,920
The train was running late.

116
00:11:36,920 --> 00:11:38,640
Besides...

117
00:11:39,880 --> 00:11:41,750
I wanted to see you.

118
00:11:42,590 --> 00:11:45,300
I'll go ahead and take a shower.

119
00:11:53,560 --> 00:11:55,190
Akina.

120
00:11:55,190 --> 00:11:58,060
Would you mind letting me go?

121
00:12:00,390 --> 00:12:01,830
Sorry.

122
00:12:02,860 --> 00:12:05,780
No worries.
I'm just a bit sweaty now, is all.

123
00:12:06,310 --> 00:12:09,450
But you're free to cling once I'm clean.

124
00:12:23,860 --> 00:12:27,300
Has everything been alright since then?

125
00:12:27,300 --> 00:12:28,610
Huh?

126
00:12:28,610 --> 00:12:31,210
That stalker. Has he been bothering you?

127
00:12:32,980 --> 00:12:36,110
Not at all. I'd forgotten about him.

128
00:12:36,770 --> 00:12:38,640
That's good to hear.

129
00:12:40,000 --> 00:12:42,400
I'll get our bath ready.

130
00:12:50,490 --> 00:12:52,700
Go all the way with me.

131
00:13:01,590 --> 00:13:04,040
I mean, what? Sorry.

132
00:13:04,040 --> 00:13:06,360
I was just kidding.

133
00:13:10,880 --> 00:13:12,170
Akina.

134
00:13:12,170 --> 00:13:15,720
Jeez, I must be pent up or something.

135
00:13:15,720 --> 00:13:17,720
I can't believe I just asked that.

136
00:13:17,720 --> 00:13:21,560
A friend said she felt great
after doing it all the way.

137
00:13:21,560 --> 00:13:24,540
She must've influenced me a bit.

138
00:13:24,540 --> 00:13:28,010
I seriously can't believe myself.

139
00:13:28,010 --> 00:13:30,740
Good night, see you next time.

140
00:14:00,190 --> 00:14:03,010
What the heck am I even doing?

141
00:14:12,820 --> 00:14:15,120
This color is beautiful.
[Love Survivors]

142
00:14:15,120 --> 00:14:18,410
I had pink in mind, but this is wonderful.

143
00:14:18,410 --> 00:14:20,330
It really is.

144
00:14:20,330 --> 00:14:23,790
I wanted the cover
to have a lasting impression,

145
00:14:23,790 --> 00:14:26,850
with the hopes that it'll become
a best-seller.

146
00:14:27,920 --> 00:14:30,960
Exactly. Our goal is a volume two.

147
00:14:30,960 --> 00:14:32,420
Really?

148
00:14:33,260 --> 00:14:37,140
But I think it'll be doable.

149
00:14:37,140 --> 00:14:40,250
Oh? You've been on a roll lately.

150
00:14:40,250 --> 00:14:43,580
I'm exploring new avenues for myself.

151
00:14:43,580 --> 00:14:44,980
Sounds potentially raunchy.

152
00:14:44,980 --> 00:14:49,060
Why? I meant it as a change in heart.

153
00:14:49,060 --> 00:14:51,770
I feel more confident in myself now.

154
00:14:52,640 --> 00:14:57,100
I was always on this side of the border,

155
00:14:57,100 --> 00:15:01,060
but I've finally stepped one foot
into the other side.

156
00:15:01,060 --> 00:15:03,280
Sorry, I'm not exactly following.

157
00:15:03,280 --> 00:15:05,900
No worries.

158
00:15:05,900 --> 00:15:08,730
What do you think of this cover?

159
00:15:12,770 --> 00:15:14,180
I'm home.

160
00:15:14,180 --> 00:15:15,300
Welcome back.

161
00:15:15,300 --> 00:15:16,840
You're early.

162
00:15:16,840 --> 00:15:20,690
Yeah. Tomorrow and the day after
are full recording sessions.

163
00:15:20,690 --> 00:15:22,310
- You're staying the night?
- Yeah.

164
00:15:22,310 --> 00:15:24,720
Sorry I've been holed up at the studio.

165
00:15:24,720 --> 00:15:29,360
Don't be. I'm looking forward to the album.

166
00:15:29,360 --> 00:15:30,940
Thanks.

167
00:15:32,040 --> 00:15:34,400
Mind if I join you for a drink?

168
00:15:40,700 --> 00:15:43,320
- Cheers.
- Cheers.

169
00:15:46,700 --> 00:15:49,020
Yum!

170
00:15:49,730 --> 00:15:54,700
<i>Ouji knows something happened to me.</i>

171
00:15:56,460 --> 00:15:58,680
Do we have any of that expensive cheese left?

172
00:15:58,680 --> 00:16:00,190
The one we got as a gift.

173
00:16:00,190 --> 00:16:02,390
I think so.

174
00:16:02,390 --> 00:16:04,370
I'll get it.

175
00:16:04,370 --> 00:16:06,400
- Thank you.
- Sure.

176
00:16:11,360 --> 00:16:18,220
<i>But he probably won't pry,
so long as it seems like I've calmed down.</i>

177
00:16:19,880 --> 00:16:21,760
We had a solid chunk left.

178
00:16:21,760 --> 00:16:23,430
Great.

179
00:16:26,240 --> 00:16:30,050
<i>This side, and that side.</i>

180
00:16:30,050 --> 00:16:33,560
<i>The border used to be so rigid, and yet...</i>

181
00:16:40,650 --> 00:16:43,500
I scare myself.

182
00:16:44,920 --> 00:16:46,800
How so?

183
00:16:47,540 --> 00:16:55,260
Before, I was so desperate to know
what he was thinking.

184
00:16:55,260 --> 00:16:59,460
But now, I can read him like a book.

185
00:16:59,460 --> 00:17:01,750
Sorry, what is this about?

186
00:17:02,690 --> 00:17:07,140
Erm... a pet.

187
00:17:07,140 --> 00:17:09,810
I don't remember you owning a pet.

188
00:17:09,810 --> 00:17:11,790
I don't.

189
00:17:11,790 --> 00:17:15,230
Then your next book will be about a pet?

190
00:17:15,230 --> 00:17:18,480
Yeah, I'm considering it.

191
00:17:18,480 --> 00:17:20,230
Can't wait to read it.

192
00:17:21,800 --> 00:17:24,060
[Busi-CAFE]

193
00:17:24,060 --> 00:17:26,280
Did something inspire you to change?

194
00:17:26,280 --> 00:17:27,640
Huh?

195
00:17:28,400 --> 00:17:33,250
You said you felt more confident.

196
00:17:34,810 --> 00:17:40,430
Right. Yeah, you could say that.

197
00:17:41,360 --> 00:17:43,610
So, what happened?

198
00:17:44,480 --> 00:17:49,230
Nothing major or life-changing, really.

199
00:17:52,240 --> 00:17:55,180
The protagonist of your book. Is she...

200
00:17:56,000 --> 00:17:58,270
Sorry, I need to take this.

201
00:17:58,270 --> 00:17:59,900
Hello?

202
00:17:59,900 --> 00:18:02,590
Oh, yes. It's good to hear from you.

203
00:18:03,720 --> 00:18:05,990
Next month?

204
00:18:07,600 --> 00:18:10,100
[Secret]

205
00:18:12,990 --> 00:18:15,230
<i>Yum!</i>

206
00:18:19,810 --> 00:18:21,690
Question.

207
00:18:23,040 --> 00:18:26,880
Do you guys prefer to know secrets?

208
00:18:27,500 --> 00:18:31,270
I mean, some things are better kept
in the dark, right?

209
00:18:31,270 --> 00:18:34,330
Yeah, I'd rather keep my secrets.

210
00:18:34,330 --> 00:18:36,970
My phone is full of them.

211
00:18:36,970 --> 00:18:39,690
Which is why I keep my phone screen down.

212
00:18:40,560 --> 00:18:43,000
- Right.
- What?

213
00:18:43,000 --> 00:18:45,040
You're keeping a secret from Haru?

214
00:18:45,040 --> 00:18:48,000
That mysterious vibe is a no-no nowadays.

215
00:18:48,000 --> 00:18:49,460
Other way around.

216
00:18:49,460 --> 00:18:51,020
Other way around?

217
00:18:52,300 --> 00:18:55,490
Haru's keeping something from you?

218
00:18:55,490 --> 00:19:00,990
That stalker - I mean,
girl obsessed with you, keeping a secret?

219
00:19:01,860 --> 00:19:03,750
Surprising.

220
00:19:03,750 --> 00:19:07,560
How can you tell? Is she acting jumpy?

221
00:19:10,160 --> 00:19:11,850
The opposite, actually.

222
00:19:11,850 --> 00:19:14,110
She's become calm.

223
00:19:14,110 --> 00:19:15,960
Like she's self-assured now.

224
00:19:15,960 --> 00:19:18,110
So you suspect a secret?

225
00:19:18,110 --> 00:19:19,810
Yeah.

226
00:19:19,810 --> 00:19:21,990
I'm surprised.

227
00:19:22,440 --> 00:19:26,320
Right? She's always been an open book.

228
00:19:26,320 --> 00:19:28,630
No, I'm surprised by you.

229
00:19:29,310 --> 00:19:34,050
You wouldn't notice something like that
if you weren't observing her.

230
00:19:35,430 --> 00:19:39,980
Question is, do you want to know her secret?

231
00:19:40,820 --> 00:19:42,930
Well...

232
00:19:44,030 --> 00:19:46,770
Not an immediate answer, I see.

233
00:19:48,390 --> 00:19:53,880
Things are going well,
so I thought I wouldn't pry.

234
00:19:53,880 --> 00:19:56,300
Really?

235
00:19:56,300 --> 00:19:59,760
We haven't fought or anything,

236
00:19:59,760 --> 00:20:01,980
so it's been peaceful.

237
00:20:01,980 --> 00:20:05,070
Then don't open Pandora's box.

238
00:20:05,070 --> 00:20:08,040
You're probably just overthinking it.

239
00:20:08,040 --> 00:20:11,360
- Exactly.
- Right?

240
00:20:11,360 --> 00:20:13,890
No, I'm really not.

241
00:20:17,710 --> 00:20:19,370
Heading out already?

242
00:20:19,370 --> 00:20:24,130
Yeah. Ouji... My husband's out tonight,

243
00:20:24,130 --> 00:20:26,830
so I thought I'd grab dinner on my way back.

244
00:20:28,720 --> 00:20:32,250
Mind if I join you?

245
00:20:36,090 --> 00:20:38,830
It's been a while
since we had dinner together.

246
00:20:38,830 --> 00:20:41,590
Yeah. The last time was
when we were both rookies.

247
00:20:41,590 --> 00:20:43,720
And now you're a full-fledged author.

248
00:20:43,720 --> 00:20:45,910
I wouldn't say that.

249
00:20:45,910 --> 00:20:50,000
Who would've thought
I'd publish a book, right?

250
00:20:51,020 --> 00:20:56,680
I always had my faith in your writing.
You deserve the recognition.

251
00:20:58,620 --> 00:20:59,930
Thanks.

252
00:20:59,930 --> 00:21:02,940
I'm just speaking my mind.

253
00:21:07,680 --> 00:21:12,850
<i>Yikes. I can totally see his love for me.</i>

254
00:21:17,250 --> 00:21:20,110
<i>This situation, it's a bit...</i>

255
00:21:20,110 --> 00:21:23,180
- Fun.
- Huh?

256
00:21:23,300 --> 00:21:28,980
Sorry, I was just thinking
it's nice hanging out with you.

257
00:21:30,270 --> 00:21:32,600
<i>And I said it.</i>

258
00:21:32,600 --> 00:21:36,180
<i>I can't believe I'm being so bold!</i>

259
00:21:37,140 --> 00:21:38,670
Haru.

260
00:21:39,980 --> 00:21:44,350
Is your book really based on
a friend's story?

261
00:21:44,350 --> 00:21:45,850
Huh?

262
00:21:46,720 --> 00:21:52,080
It felt more like you were writing about
your own experiences.

263
00:21:55,190 --> 00:21:57,310
Well...

264
00:21:57,310 --> 00:21:58,930
If...

265
00:21:59,820 --> 00:22:05,210
If everything you wrote about is true...

266
00:22:08,800 --> 00:22:12,660
Then you should end that marriage
while you can.

267
00:22:15,530 --> 00:22:19,210
No, but I...

268
00:22:21,660 --> 00:22:27,190
The protagonist feels relieved now.

269
